name: Giyur Food Stall
address: FC63+594, Jl. Baladewa, Semarapura Kangin, Kec. Klungkung, Kabupaten Klungkung, Bali 80761, Indonesia
review 1:
HALAL FOOD

went here by accident, as we are looking for authentic Srombotan khas Klungkung. we are first timer ate Srombotan and it turn very very tasty! we also tried Nasi Sisit Sambal Matah, and it was amazing!

Price are really affordable for what it is. we spent 23K Rupiah for 3 dishes!

generous portion and lovely staff. they have big menu and all looks great, definitely will coming back to try other dishes!
review 2: My fav place to get any kind of traditional veg dishes from Klungkung.
review 3: Good place for eating balinese food

name: Lalapan Bu Dewa Sambal Leak
address: FC52+3VM, Jl. Kecubung, Semarapura Kelod, Kec. Klungkung, Kabupaten Klungkung, Bali 80711, Indonesia
review 1:
Well uh, I'll make this quick :
+cheap price. the list are :
-18000 for chicken rice
-15000 for catfish rice
-3000 additional rice
-2000 ice tea
+fast serving table

-No parking lot for cars. (You must parked on sideways)
-The outdoor tables kinda unmanaged and poor quality
-Nothing special about the cuisine

This just a quick choice for you if you really hungry and decide to eat. But it could be crowded at night so you better act fast.

Here's some of photo I've taken when eating on the outside table with my friend
review 2: Nice food,  graet taste.  Just try
review 4: This is really afordable and also spicy delicious foods

name: Tourism Village Kamasan

review 1: What a great place to learn such an amaizing balinese culture of traditional paintings. The paintings has a special style called Kamasan Paintings. Other than that, there is also another art like art carved gold, silver and even bullet
review 2: Pretty village with many artists producing kamasan-style arts (mostly painting). Recommended if you are into art and look for something unique and "authentic Balinese" to bring back home
review 3: The center of classical puppet painting activities known as puppet kamasan paintings, Also as a center of handicraft money kepeng (pis bolong).
